FBIS3-36432 "drsov025_l_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-025 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Feb 1994 Kyrgyzstan Decree Demands Payment Up-Front for Goods PM0402172194 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 3 Feb 94 First Edition p 6 PM0402172194 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Unattributed report from ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA, ITAR-TASS, and LOGOTIP-KP column under the general heading: "One-Liners"] [Text] Kyrgyzstan -- The republic's government has adopted a decree which requires manufacturing enterprises to dispatch output, raw materials, or semimanufactures only after prepayment by their customers. At the same time maximum timeframes for processing payments -- from three to seven banking days -- have been set. A fine of double the rate of interest for every day's delay will henceforth be exacted for any holdup.
